{"profile":{"awsPrograms":[{"joinedAt":2026.0,"programName":"USER_GROUP_LEADER"},{"category":"Community Hero","joinedAt":2019.0,"memberStatus":"ACTIVE","programName":"HERO"}],"basicInfo":{"alias":"maciejlelusz","avatar":"https://avatars.builderprofile.aws.dev/2zgkVoRHlhlufp2HwWYD8Pf7Kjq.webp","bio":"Hi, I’m Maciej Lelusz - consultant, architect, and occasional tech therapist. I spend my time wrangling cloud and datacenter infrastructure, convincing organizations that IT transformation isn’t just a buzzword, and reminding people that \"lift and shift\" is not a strategy.\n\nAs an AWS Community Hero, I balance hands-on architecture work with community mischief: running meetups, speaking at events, writing blog posts that call it like it is, and podcasting about the good, the bad, and the absurd parts of enterprise tech.\n\nI care deeply about creating better experiences with technology - though I may roll my eyes while doing it. Whether it’s storage design or culture change, I’m here to make IT a little smarter, a little more human, and way less boring.\n\nWant more insight, or a war story or two? Stay connected: https://lelusz.com","builderProfileId":"c2969536-ad8a-4f74-9021-b3e8375d67ee","createdOn":1.717515452416E12,"headline":"Mostly techie, sometimes manager","isStaff":false,"name":"Maciek Lelusz"},"location":{"displayLocation":{"countryRegion":"PL"}},"profileStatus":"ACTIVE","socials":{}}}